#note I decided to ditch the J instead of playing TODAY and holding it, because I didn't see great J plays I could draw. Interestingly, JOYED bingos more, but JADED and JAPED both sim better due to the great scoring plays they can draw into (JAPED keeps TODAY, JADED...uh...not sure).
>Tarin: ABOTW 11G B.W.T +34 252
>JD: DEIPSTY 2B DI.TY +38 285
#note A good reminder not to auto-pilot - the pool is extraordinarily heavy on vowels (24/43), and so DICEY keeping PST bingos more often next turn than keeping EPS! But even better, Q loves a PYAS fish that keeps DEIST and avoids getting too far into this strange unseen tile pool.
>Tarin: EGILNOR I11 ..G +9 261
>JD: AEEEEPS 6D .EE +14 299
#note I inferred WOG as a sign of him having the case S, but as evidenced by his actual bingo, that doesn't have to be the case. I also picked up on the vowel shortage around this point in the game and so chose to keep AEEPS instead of AES to retain an extra consonant - but Q disapproves because AEEPS just isn't very strong, and there is an unseen blank that I could draw. EPEE may also be extra good given that Tarin has a strong leave, because maybe some of his fishes can only bingo on column I, and might get blocked by EPEE.
>Tarin: EIILNOR 1F NOILIER +79 340
>JD: AEEHPSV B6 HAVE +31 330
#note Q hates this play, and rightly so - I give Tarin SO MANY POINTS if he has the K, or even a U. In fact, I didn't even think of the U when I played it. I rejected SHEAVE because I wanted to keep the S lane on row 14 open, but there are goodies to be drawn in the bag, and there are no Ds left so Tarin can't score too much in response to SHEAVE. All in all, a lousy play!
>Tarin: ETU A8 UTE +33 373
>JD: ?ENOPSU 8H .UtOPENS +86 416
#note I am tempted in hindsight to just play something like POUNCES at 4F that keeps the board very tight, instead of AUTOPENS which opens a ton of lanes. But after POUNCES I'm only up 33, so I don't think I can afford to sacrifice the points.
>Tarin: ILO 1A OIL +14 387
>JD: FHIIKLN 13K FILK +31 447
#note I chose FILK to block row 13 and force Tarin to empty the bag with his next play. In exchange, I let Tarin get a lot of bingos on column M and N that KIF at 9K would've blocked. My bet was that I could outrun those - Tarin's out-plays are possibly worth more with two tiles than with a single tile.
>Tarin: ACGIISU O7 I. +2 389
